For day 4️⃣ of #legendsofthepose  #yogachallenge @alomoves & @aloyoga , the asana of the day is #marichyasana .

After having read the story about this asana on @yogaandchaigirl today’s post, I have decided to pick up a picture from my YTT in Kineta.
I have learned that “ Marichi” in Sanskrit means “ Ray of Light”.
And I immediately thought about my beloved friend @monimo0305 . I have spent such a amazing time in Greece 2 weeks ago with her. She definitely was my Ray of Light during our summer journey 🥰
And I remember 2 years ago, in the same country where we first met. Everyday she was the first woman I have got to see early in the morning before our very early practice and she always had this shining and radiant smile on her face. She was my first Ray of Light of the day. And during our two weeks in Peloponnese, I have found it back 😊 my Ray of Light from Milano ☺️

That’s the reason why I have picked this picture up. It’s a great symbol of our true and sincere friendship which has started in June 2018 and which will last forever ever ever 💋💋💋❤️❤️❤️

Miss you so much Monica. Cannot wait to visit you in your beautiful country 😘

💕 Love you my friend 💕

